{"lemma":"ر","slug":"ر","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"abbrev","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["character","symbol","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14240"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"character","gloss":"The tenth letter of the Arabic alphabet, called رَاء (rāʔ) and written in the Arabic script; preceded by ذ (ḏ) and followed by ز (z).","tags":["letter"]},{"pos":"symbol","gloss":"The twentieth numeral symbol of the Arabic alphabet (traditional abjad order, used for list numbering), written in the Arabic script; preceded by ق (q) and followed by ش (š)."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the Nabataean letter 𐢛 (l, “resh”), derived from the Phoenician letter 𐤓 (l, “resh”), from the Egyptian hieroglyph 𓁶. See also Classical Syriac ܪ (l, “resh”), Hebrew ר (l, “resh”), Ancient Greek Ρ (R), Latin R."},"ipa":["/raːʔ/","/r/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14240","headword_ar":"ر","root":"r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tenth letter of the alphabet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA='N","text_ar":"رَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA","text_ar":"رَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAA=tN","text_ar":"رَاا=تٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaA='N","text_ar":"اَرْوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb AlAlf Ally~nh","text_ar":"باب الالف الليّنه"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is one of the letters termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majohuwrap","text_ar":"مَجْهُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or vocal, i. e. pronounced with the voice, not with the breath only]; and of the letters termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uloq","text_ar":"ذُلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awolaqiy~ap","text_ar":"ذَوْلَقِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or pronounced with the extremity of the tongue, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afahiy~ap","text_ar":"شَفَهِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or pronounced with the lips:] these letters which are pronounced with the tip of the tongue and with the lips abound in the composition of Arabic words: (L:) and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed, in a vulgar prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaAru Al$uEaraA='i","text_ar":"حِمَارُ الشُعَرَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ the ass of the poets ”]. (TA in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAb AlAlf All~ynp","text_ar":"باب الالف اللّينة"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"navorapN","text_ar":"نَثْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"navolapN","text_ar":"نَثْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raEal~a","text_ar":"رَعَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEal~a","text_ar":"لَعَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajirN","text_ar":"وَجِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awojaru","text_ar":"اَوْجَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajilN","text_ar":"وَجِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awojalu","text_ar":"اَوْجَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this substitution is a peculiarity of the dial. of Keys; wherefore some assert that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in these cases is an original radical letter. (MF.)       -A2-  [As a numeral, it denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two hundred."},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["L"]}]}}